<p>In today's live lesson you wrote your own <code>draw_ship</code> code. Now record a short video on your phone explaining the code <strong>you</strong> wrote. You may show it running. Try to use these words: <strong>function</strong>, <strong>define</strong>, <strong>call</strong>, <strong>parameter</strong>, <strong>nose</strong>.</p>
<blockquote>
<ol>
<li>Show your ship and point at its nose.</li>
<li>Read your <code>def draw_ship(x)</code> line out loud and explain what the parameter does.</li>
<li>Point at the line where you <strong>call</strong> the function.</li>
